arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
5.70 m north south -by- 5.80 m east west.

Locus 16 is the debris just above the floor of the “entrance room.” It is a fine dark brown silt (Munsell 7.5 YR 3/3) with inclusions of ash and pottery, as well as significant numbers of ashlars and marble tile fragments. These marble fragments are most likely pieces from the walls and floor (Locus 60) of the room which were dislodged during the collapse of the bath complex.
Collapse and wash above the floor in the “entrance room”
